{
  "stem": "1363.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "By that time, it got-- we got back to Budapest, that was after the boarding schools.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As well, by then in a public school, which was very close to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was just a normal public school where Jews were there and non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I lost the thread.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With Grandma and my auntie.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maternal-- my paternal stayed in Bratislava.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my maternal was the one where my brother, Fredi, and my mother came-- my father, for all I know-- to Hungary from Wunstorf, right?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I stayed with Grandma-- yeah, the paternal grandma.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we stayed in, in Budapest with my maternal relatives, with my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father wasn't there anymore, right?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He went to Brussels.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we went to school until I was 14.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the meantime, my auntie gave birth to a daughter, Vera, whom I adored.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I, I really always, my ambition was to get-- to become a mother, to push the pram of a baby.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I somehow felt I had so much affection and love to give to someone that that little baby in the pram was the only one whom I can give it to.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because my mother was a very sick person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 85,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She had angina pectoris, which meant that she had a problem with the heart-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't know how you say that in English.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A very weak heart-- as a child she had scarlet fever.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was left over from a weak heart.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, the knowledge that her husband wasn't with her and that it didn't look very kosher in those days, the Hungarian situation with the Jews.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She always was afraid that she won't see him anymore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she went down the hill emotionally.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 86,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And with emotional came the sickness.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
